import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Delay Time')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the average distance
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()

    # Create a bar chart of distance
    plt.bar(['Average Distance'], [avg_distance], color='blue')

    # Add a horizontal line for the average distance
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')

    # Set the chart title
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)

    # Add a legend
    plt.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    origin_destination_counts = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    origin_destination_counts = origin_destination_counts.sort_values('counts', ascending=False)
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    origin_destination_counts.plot(kind='bar', x=['origin', 'destination'], y='counts', ax=ax, legend=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin and Destination')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common origin and destination for flights?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'])
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Delay')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between delay time and distance?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    flights_by_date = data.groupby('date').size()
    
    plt.plot(flights_by_date.index, flights_by_date.values)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights by date?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
